 Port Elizabeth - Some good rains were recorded overnight across the Eastern Cape and the Southern Cape, the Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service said on Thursday. Most of the rain was recorded at Plettenberg Bay (25mm) and at the Flower Reserve in Port Elizabeth (21mm). "Some nice soaking rain was recorded overnight over the coastal areas and adjacent interior," said Garth Sampson, the SA Weather Service's Client Liaison Officer for the Eastern Cape. Station Names 5 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 7.2 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 7.6 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 10.8 AWSH Chatty * AWS Coega 2.8 AWSH Fettes Road 4.4 ARS Flower Reserve 21.0 AWSH Motherwell * ARS Riverstone Bridge 10.4 ARS St Albans 11.4 AWS Uitenhage * Man Woodridge 16.5 Catchment  AWS Joubertina 0.4 Man Kareedouw 6.5 Man Kouga Dam 3.0 AWS Patensie 2.6 Man Swartkops  * Man   Other Towns  AWS Addo 1.2 AWS Bisho/KWT 1.0 AWS Cape St Francis 2.8 AWS Cradock NIL AWS East London 6.2 AWS Fort Beaufort 0.4 AWS George 4.5 AWS Graaff Reinet NIL AWS Grahamstown NIL AWS Henry`s Flats NIL AWS Joubertina 0.4 AWS Mossel Bay 3.0 AWS Mthatha 3.8 AWS Plettenberg Bay 25.0 AWS Port Alfred 8.0 AWS Queenstown NIL  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 